What’s interesting (your insight)

These layers don’t just stack—they:

interlock and compensate for each other

When one fails:
	•	another catches it
	•	or limits the damage

⸻

Why API keys feel “simple but dangerous”

Because they collapse multiple layers into one:

Possession = permission

That’s powerful… and fragile.

